  "prompt": "How can I dress for a foam party?",
  "response": "When dressing for a foam party, consider the following tips:\n\n1. Wear something that can get wet and won't be ruined:\n- Quick-drying materials like swimwear\n- Lightweight, synthetic fabrics\n- Shorts and tank tops\n- Swimsuits\n- Old t-shirts and shorts\n\n2. Choose clothing that:\n- Won't become see-through when wet\n- Is comfortable and allows movement\n- Won't restrict you in the foam\n\n3. Footwear:\n- Water-resistant sandals\n- Waterproof shoes\n- Crocs\n- Flip-flops\n\n4. Things to avoid:\n- Expensive or delicate clothing\n- White or light-colored clothes (they might become transparent)\n- Tight or restrictive clothing\n- Jeans (they become heavy when wet)\n\n5. Additional tips:\n- Bring a change of dry clothes\n- Pack a plastic bag for wet items\n- Consider wearing waterproof makeup\n- Remove valuable jewelry\n- Bring a towel\n\nRemember to prioritize comfort and practicality while having fun and staying safe.",
